{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"846ef586-fc0a-4a13-a1d8-bbf0b6671d2b","content":"Yes, you'll hit **target framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 drops support for:\n\n- **`net5.0`** — .NET 5 is end-of-life; you'd need to move to `net6.0` or later.\n- **`net462`** — .NET Framework older than 4.6.2 is dropped, but your `net462` is exactly at the boundary. However, depending on the MSTest v3 minor version, `net462` *may* require updating to `net472` or higher — check the release notes.\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — .NET Core 3.1 is end-of-life and no longer supported.\n\n**Before upgrading**, you'll need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to supported versions (e.g., `net6.0;net472` or `net8.0;net472`).\n\nWould you like me to run the full MSTest v2→v3 migration skill to handle all the changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cbdc88d2-6c25-4c3c-850e-c2d3b7515320","outputTokens":238,"requestId":"0420:1CF5FA:22A8EC2:2746FAA:69E83212"},"id":"a5c0e7eb-6b99-47c0-ac41-74c5ba333bdb","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:27:37.240Z","parentId":"f16cb323-4590-4f8c-bfbc-28c7caf9584f"}
